the user uploads the scanned payment

steps.name: a pending manual payment exists

elements.name: 4. Processed manual payment attached to the offset is displayed upon approval

elements.name: 6. User cancels approval to process a manual payment

elements.name: 7. User rejects manual payment

the manual payment status is updated to 'REJECTED'.

the manual payment status is not updated to 'REJECTED'.

description:
This feature allows the workflow of Rejecting, Updating and Deleting a Pending Reversal Online to occur. Given a pending reversal exists the workfow is as follows:

1. TOP Administrator or TOP Accounting role Rejects a Reversal Online via View Offset Details screen
2. Email notification is sent to TOP View user to inform them of Rejected Reversal - Deferred 
3. TOP View will Update or Delete Reversal via the View Offset Details screen
4. Email notification is sent to TOP Administrator and/or TOP Accounting (Depends who rejected reversal) to inform them of Updated or Deleted Reversal - Deferred
5. If TOP View Deletes the Reversal Request the Pending Reversal Data will be deleted and no longer available for approval.
6. If Pending Reversal was updated the TOP Administrator Reviews and Approve the Pending Reversal Information is correct. 
7. If TOP Administrator approves it will continue the Request Reversal workflow and become available for TOP Acccounting to approve.
